Coronavirus travel health
Check the latest information on risk from COVID-19 for the Cook Islands on the TravelHealthPro website.
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
Entry and borders
See Entry requirements to find out what you will need to do when you arrive in the Cook Islands.
Travel in the Cook Islands
There are no domestic travel restrictions in place in the Cook Islands. The governmentâ€™s recommendations on physical distancing and good hygiene measures remain in place, see the Cook Islands COVID-19 website for further detail.
Healthcare in the Cook Islands
For health-related questions or concerns while in the Cook Islands, call the Healthline on 0800 1801.
Finance
For information on financial support you can access whilst abroad, visit our financial assistance guidance.
Returning to the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK.
Further information
Further information on these and the wider situation in the Cook Islands is available from the Cook Islands COVID-19 website and the Cook Islands Ministry of Health website.
